(108519, ' Reviewing the posts, I would like to add that it is beretta which added/copied/followed two distinct features of Taurus that are 1) The original PT92 was exactly like the original Beretta 92, though it was also unusual for the time in that it featured a squared trigger guard for supporting the index finger of the opposite hand while firing, a feature which was subsequently introduced to the Beretta 92 with the 92SB-F (92F) model in 1985. 2) Taurus has begun manufacturing the PT92 with built-in accessory rails on the frame, a feature found on the newer M9A1 pistol. Also note that PT92 is official sidearm of; The PT92 is the standard sidearm of the Brazilian Army beside Imbel 1911, Military Police and Força Nacional de Segurança Pública (in military service, it is known as the M975 pistol) & in Dominican Republic used by the Dominican Navy.', ''),
