(111254, ' As per my knowledge hunting for MUSLIMS is allowed only if they hunt to eat otherwise it is forbidden …………. this what I have been taught during the early days of hunting by my father\n\nObserving law is the best solution. As per law only bag limit is not defined but also the number of hunters for a particular shoot is defined. Going for a partridge shoot with 10 gun (shooters) and 20 beaters is illegal as per law in Punjab for a hunting party on a partridge shoot max. 3 shooters with 10 beaters are allowed beyond this everything is illegal therefore bag above 18 partridges is illegal in any case\n\nAs far as Wild boars are concerned they are “enemy of humanity so kill them” this is what written on the shooting license. In Pakistan the population of wild boars is enormous and every year they ruin crops valued in millions if calculated country wide. After shooting usually boars are left where they are killed but burying them is good idea if not sold are given to non-muslims', ''),
